Absa, Afrox, Gold Fields, Investec: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-05-18T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/absa-afrox-gold-fields-investec-south-africa-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index dropped 312.10, or 1
percent, to 31,843.91 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg on May
17. Markets were closed yesterday for local government
elections.  Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  : The investment banking unit of
South Africa’s largest retail bank holds a press conference on
its future plans at 9:30 a.m. in Johannesburg. Absa fell 68
cents, or 0.5 percent, to 135.35 rand.  African Oxygen Ltd. (AFX)  : Africa’s largest producer of
industrial gases holds its annual general meeting at 10 a.m. in
Johannesburg. Afrox, as it’s known, added 5 cents, or 0.3
percent, to 18.70 rand.  Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  : South Africa’s second-
largest coal producer holds its annual general meeting at 9 a.m.
in Johannesburg. Exxaro slipped 1.75 rand, or 1.1 percent, to
164 rand.  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  : The world’s fourth-largest
producer of the metal releases first-quarter earnings. Gold
Fields lost 2.51 rand, or 2.3 percent, to 106.74 rand.  Investec Ltd. (INL)  : The owner of a private bank and
money manager with operations in South Africa, the U.K. and
 Australia , releases fiscal full-year earnings. The stock climbed
8 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 52.75 rand.  Pinnacle Point Group Ltd. (PNG)  : The owner of golf
resorts said it sold its Pinnacle Point Golf and Beach Resorts
business for 75 million rand ($11 million) to Veritable
Investments Ltd. and Raptoguard Ltd. to settle debt of 58
million rand to Investec. Pinnacle Point was unchanged at 1
cent.  Reunert Ltd. (RLO)  : The maker of electric power cables
and telecommunications equipment said its second-half
performance will beat the first six months of its fiscal year,
when net income increased to 789.8 million rand from 398.6
million rand. Reunert decreased 69 cents, or 1.2 percent, to
59.50 rand.  SacOil Holding Ltd. (SCL)  : The South Africa-based oil
and gas explorer will announce an “enhancement” to its
internal management team within about a week aimed at helping
the company grow on the continent, Chief Executive Officer Robin Vela said at a conference in Nairobi. The company’s share price
will “come back” to better reflect the value of SacOil’s
assets, Vela said. SacOil declined 2 cents, or 1.3 percent, to
1.48 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vernon Wessels in Johannesburg at 
